<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/859</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>285. Your No. 93, September 27, 9 p.m. It would serve a highly useful
                                purpose if you could obtain permission for the Department to publish
                                this statement of <persName corresp="#p_DCC1">De
                                    Broqueville</persName>. The Department assumes that the
                                “postscript” refers to a report from Berne given out by the wireless
                                press September 25 stating that Germany agreed to evacuate Belgium
                                on certain conditions. This report said that there was a verbal
                                communication from <persName corresp="#p_KRV1">Kühlmann</persName>
                                to the Papal Nuncio at Munich.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>